<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-12 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
        <h1 class="location_title_on">
            <%= @location.title %>
        </h1>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-8 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
        <div class="row ">          
            <figure class="col-md-12 col-xs-12 col-xs-12"> 
                <div id="carousel-example-generic" class="carousel slide gallery" data-ride="carousel"  >
                    <div class="carousel-inner" >
                        <div class="item active" >
                            <%= image_tag @location.image.url, class:"img-thumbnail", alt:"gallery image" %>
                        </div> 
                        <% @photos.each do |photo| %>
                        <div class="item" >
                            <%= image_tag photo.photo.url, class:"img-thumbnail", alt:"gallery image" %>
                        </div>  
                        <% end %>                      
                    </div>   
                    <a class="left carousel-control" href="#carousel-example-generic" role="button" data-slide="prev">
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-left" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                            <span class="sr-only">Previous</span>
                    </a>
                    <a class="right carousel-control" href="#carousel-example-generic" role="button" data-slide="next">
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-chevron-right" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                        <span class="sr-only">Next</span>
                    </a>          
                </div>  
            </figure>
            <div class="col-md-6 col-xs-6 text-center">     
                <%= link_to like_location_path(@location), :class => "btn btn-default form-control like-btn" do %>
                    <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-thumbs-up glyph-black" ></span>        
                <% end %>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6 col-xs-6 text-center"> 
                <%= link_to dislike_location_path(@location), :class => "btn btn-default form-control like-btn" do %>
                    <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-thumbs-down glyph-black"></span>
                <% end %>
            </div>
          
            <div class="col-md-12 col-xs-12">
                <article>
                    <h2> 
                        1.) Description
                    </h2>
                    <% if @location.title!="Bojnice Castle" %>
                        <%= @location.description %>
                    <% else %>    
                        <p>
                            The gem of Bojnice is the ”fairy-tale” Bojnický zámok Castle, one of the most visited and most beautiful castles not only in Slovakia, but also in central Europe.
                            It is a Romantic castle with some original Gothic and Renaissance elements built in the 12th century.
                        </p>

                        <p>
                            The castle is renowned for its attractions, including the popular Castle Fairytale, the International Festival of Ghosts and Spirits and the Summer Music Festival.
                            The romantic castle is also a popular location for filming fairy tale movies, such as Fantaghirò.
                        </p>

                        <h2> 
                            2.) My tour 
                        </h2>

                        <p>
                            I visited the castle with my family and we chose the night tour. It lasted 90 minutes and the kids enjoyed it pretty much. 
                            It was non-traditional <em>"Night Tour the castle with ghosts and spooks"</em> with lecturer in period costumes, sometimes just under candle light, enriched by an old castle legends and rumors.
                            Interesting for us was <em>Golden Hall</em> too. The most representative room of Bojnice castle. Angelic ceiling is gilded with pure gold and the most valuable paintings adorned the walls. 
                        </p>

                        <p>
                            During the day we visited the <em>natural cave</em> situated in a travertine hill on which the castle is built. 
                            The cave has a diameter of 22 meters, a height of 6 meters and there are two pools (depth 8-12 m).
                            Around Bojnice castle is a natural <em>landscape park</em>, a good place for a walk, there are a number of rare and interesting trees e.g. <em>Lipa King Matthias</em>. 
                            Charming was our view from <em>the tower</em> too. 
                        </p>


                        <p>
                            Next time we would like to visit <em>International Festival of Ghosts and Monsters</em>, it is among the largest event of its kind in the world and is visited by over 50,000 tourists.
                            The castle complex is then filled with various temptations, attractions, fearsome atmosphere and good humor, of course, food stalls and various goodies.
                            The event is always conceived as a story in which the audience is drawn in the tour of the castle. 
                        </p>


                        <h2> 3.) Calendar of Events for year 2016: </h2>
                            <p>
                                <strong>Programme is only in Slovak language. </strong>
                            </p>
                        <p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>VALENTINE´S WEEKEND IN CASTLE   <strong>12. 2. - 13. 2. 2016 </strong></li>
                                <li>INTERNATIONAL FESTIVAL OF GHOSTS AND SPIRITS <strong> 27. 4. - 30. 4. 2016 </strong> && <strong>  4. 5. - 8. 5. 2016 </strong></li>
                                <li>THE FAIRYTALE CASTLE <strong>15. 6. - 19. 6. 2016 </strong> && <strong> 22. 6. - 26. 6. 2016 </strong></li>
                                <li>SUPER NIGHT AT THE CASTLE <strong> 12. 8. - 14. 8. 2016 </strong> </li>
                                <li>JACK-O'-LANTERN AT THE BOJNICE CASTLE <strong> 28. - 29. 10. a 31. 10. 2016 at 7 pm. </strong></li>
                                <li>St. NICHOLAS AND CHRISTMAS IN BOJNICE CASTLE <strong> 4. 12. - 5. 12. 2015 - St. NICHOLAS 8. 12. 2015 - 6. 1. 2016 </strong></li>
                            </ul>
                        </p>

                        <h2> 4.) Services </h2>

                        <p>
                            Renting of the apartment for one day          650,00 €
                            The rent includes operating costs based on the character of the rent.
                            The bookings for room hire send in writing to the Department for Marketing and Services (rezervacie@bojnicecastle.sk ).
                        </p>

                        <h2>5.) Related: </h2>
                        <h3>5.1)<a href="#">  Castle park </a></h3>
                        <h3>5.2)<a href="#"> Park Zoo </a></h3>
                        <h3>5.3)<a href="#"> Bojnice Baths </a></h3>
                    <% end %>
                </article>
                <div id="comments">
                    <h3 class="comment_count">
                        <%= pluralize(@location.comments.count, "Comment") %>
                    </h3>
                    <% @comments.each do |comment| %>
                        <div class="comment">
                            <p class="username">
                                <%= link_to comment.user.name, comment.user %> comented on <%= comment.created_at.strftime('%d %B %Y') %>:
                            </p>
                            <p class="content">
                                "<%= comment.content %>"
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    <% end %>
                    <%= render "comments/form" %>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4 col-xs-12">
        <div class="row">
            <aside class="col-md-12 col-xs-12 col-sm-12">
                <ul class="list-group">
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-user glyph-aside"></span> 
                        <%= link_to @location.user.name, @location.user %>
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        <%= link_to like_location_path(@location), :class => "btn" do %>
                            <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-thumbs-up glyph-aside-like"></span>
                        <% end %>
                        <%= @location.get_upvotes.size %> Likes
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        <%= link_to dislike_location_path(@location), :class => "btn" do %>
                            <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-thumbs-down glyph-aside-like"></span>
                        <% end %>
                        <%= @location.get_downvotes.size %> Dislikes 
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-map-marker glyph-aside"></span>
                        Lon <%= @location.lon %>, Lat <%= @location.lat %>
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item" style="padding-left:13px">
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon glyphicon-tags glyph-aside"></span>
                        <% @location.tag_list.each do |tag| %>
                            <span class="badge tag">
                            <%= link_to tag, "category/"+tag %>
                            </span>
                        <% end %>
                    </li>
                    <% if user_signed_in? %>
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <%= simple_form_for [@location, @location.photos.build] do |f| %>
                                <%= f.input :photo, label: "Add Photo to this location", required: true, input_html: { class: 'form-control' }, wrapper_html: { class: 'form-group' } %>
                                <%= f.button :submit,"Add Photo", class: "btn" %>
                            <% end %>
                        </li>
                        <% if current_user.name==@location.user.name %>
                            <li class="list-group-item">
                                <%= link_to "Edit Location", edit_location_path(@location) , class: "btn btn-success edit_btn form-control", style:"margin-bottom: 10px;"%>
                                <%= link_to "Delete Location!", location_path(@location), method: :delete, data: {confirm: "Are you sure?"}, class: "btn btn-danger edit_btn form-control" %>
                            </li>
                        <% end %>
                    <% end %>
                </ul>
            </aside>
            <aside class="col-md-12 col-xs-12 col-sm-12">
                <div id="map_small">
                </div>
            </aside>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<%= render "gmaps_show" %>




